{{See|Gay}}
==English==
=== Etymology ===
Possibly from Latin ''[[gaudium]]'', "joy".
The word is known to have been adopted through the French ''[[gai]]'' in 12th century. Other Romance languages had a sense of "slack", "not closely fitting", but its etymological importance is not understood.
It is unclear where the word originally came from. Some, such as [[w:Friedrich Christian Diez|Friedrich Christian Diez]], suggested that it comes from Middle High German.
The sense of "homosexual" is said to have come from an Arabic word via French; it is also said to come from the word's older sense of "dissolute".

